                "invention-title": [
                    "Preparation method and application of nickel-modified copper-based monatomic alloy oxide nanowire",
                    "镍修饰铜基单原子合金氧化物纳米线制备方法及其应用"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a preparation method of a nickel-modified copper-based monatomic alloy oxide nanowire and application of the nanowire to ammonia preparation through electro-catalysis of nitrate reduction, and the catalyst shows excellent catalytic performance of ammonia preparation through electro-catalysis of nitrate reduction in an alkaline medium. Thories and experiments prove that the surface of the copper-based oxide nanowire modified by nickel monatomic sites promotes the dissociation process of water on the surface of the copper-based oxide nanowire, the number of active hydrogen species on the surface of the copper-based oxide nanowire is increased, and reaction energy barriers for converting an intermediate * NO2 into * NOOH and converting * NO into * NOH are reduced; therefore, the hydrogenation reaction of an intermediate * NO2 during ammonia preparation through electro-catalysis nitrate radical reduction is promoted. The generation of a by-product NO2 &lt;-&gt; formed by desorption of * NO2 is reduced, and the capability of converting NO2 &lt;-&gt; into NH3 is enhanced, so that excellent activity and selectivity of reducing nitrate to prepare ammonia are obtained."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了镍修饰铜基单原子合金氧化物纳米线的制备方法及其应用于电催化硝酸根还原制氨，该催化剂在碱性介质中表现出了优异的电催化硝酸根还原制氨的催化性能，理论和实验证明镍单原子位点修饰的铜基氧化物纳米线表面促进了铜基氧化物纳米线表面水的解离过程，提高了其表面的活性氢物种的数量，降低了中间体*NO2转化为*NOOH和*NO转化为*NOH的反应能垒，从而促进了电催化硝酸根还原制氨时中间体*NO2的加氢反应。减少了由于*NO2脱附而形成的副产物NO2‑的生成，增强了其将NO2‑转化为NH3的能力，从而获得了优异的硝酸根还原制氨的活性和选择性。"
                }
            ]
